            <p>1.1. Check monitor displays and make sure they are set to at least the minimum supported display resolution of 1024 x 768 pixels. To do this open up control panel and hit the display button.</p>
            <p>1.2. To take advantage of email and text-message capabilities Microsoft Outlook or later must be installed and configured on each computer. Outlook is properly configured if able to send and receive emails.
                 Instructions on how to install Microsoft Outlook are available later in this guide, at this point you just want to make sure the software is available in your browsers computer.</p>
            <p>1.3. All other system and hardware requirements: </p>
            <ul class="no-list-type">
                <li>- not dependable on operating system, works on  Windows, Mac or Linux</li>
                <li>- required Mozilla Firefox or Google Chrome browser installed, on Chrome it runs faster</li>
                <li>- compatible on any tablet device as well on any PC computer</li>
                <li>- dosen't require free space on harddrive, all the data is stored on servers </li>
                <li>- 1 Gb Ram Minimum, 2 Gb Reccomended. for smooth navigation</li>
                <li>- minimum display resolution - 1024x768, works excelent on 1920x1080</li>
                <li>- no cdrom required, no installations required</li>
                <li>- required for reports "Adobe Reader" or any sort of *.pdf reader</li>
                <li>- compatible with lase, inkjet or most thermal receipt printers with the condition of these to be installed</li>
            </ul>
