            <h4>9. Grooming setup</h4>
            <hr />
            <p>
                There are two basic types of grooming in the application: Baths and Haircuts.
                These names can be changed in the set up. Within each of these types you can configure an unlimited number
                of sub-types, such as good shape, small dog, etc. <br /><br />
                <h5><strong>Grooming general</strong></h5>
                9.1.  Go to "Options" -> "Reservation" -> "Reservation options" -> "Grooming" -> "General"
            </p>
            <hr />
            <p>9.1.1 <strong>Grooming options</strong> <br /><br />
                * To print the recommended next grooming appointment date in invoices, check the option ‘Recommended Next Groom in Use.(Appears in Bill)’
                For example, if a pet was groomed on the first of November and the system is set up to recommend every 4 weeks, the invoice will have a
                recommended next groom date for the first of December. <br />
                <br />
                * The Recommended Next Groom in Use has a selectable option for how many weeks between the next grooming. <br />
                <br />
                * Define the groomer limit option. If a groomer will be scheduled in a day depending on the number of pets,
                  select the option ‘Groomer Limit as number of pets.' If a groomer will be scheduled in a day depending
                  on the number of grooming hours they can perform, select the option ‘Groomer Limit as hours.’ <br />
                <br />
                * Define ‘Base Type 1’ and ‘Base Type 2’ grooming types. We recommend using ‘Bath’ and ‘Hair Cut’
                    for type’s 1 and 2 respectively; however, the two main grooming types can be labeled as desired.
                    In this set up guide, we will refer to ‘Base 1’ and ‘Base 2’ as ‘Baths’ and ‘Hair Cuts’ for simplicity.
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.1.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <hr />
            <p>9.1.2 <strong>Groomer priority by breed</strong> <br /><br />
                Groomer Priority by Breed allows you to schedule new pets to a groomer that specializes in that breed.
                Select a groomer and then select a breed and assign the priority of 1. New pets and pets not assigned
                a ‘preferred groomer’ of that breed will automatically be assigned to that groomer if she is available.
                You can choose a different groomer within the program.
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.2.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <hr />
            <p>9.1.3 <strong>Pet breed setup</strong> <br /><br />
                * you specify in hours and 15 minute increments the amount of time to be allowed for a bath or a haircut.
                Use the set all baths and set all haircut buttons to apply one time to all breeds.
                This should be an average amount of time that applies to many breeds.
                To modify the time for specific breeds use the search breed window
                to find the breed and change the amount of time needed to groom that breed.
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.3.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <br />
            <hr />
                <h5><strong>Grooming rates</strong></h5>
            <p>
                9.2.  Go to "Options" -> "Reservation" -> "Reservation options" -> "Grooming" -> "Rates"
            </p>
            <p>
                9.2.1. <strong> Hourly rates</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
                9.2.1.1. If you want the system to automatically assign a rate to each grooming reservation, check the option
                  ‘In Use (Suggests automatically base price for grooming reservations).’ If not checked the grooming
                  price will initially be set to 0. The main advantage of NOT using this feature is that if a grooming
                  price is set up with a 0.00 rate, the system will alert you when checking out that there is no price
                for that groom. Otherwise, if a rate was already pre-assigned by default the system will not produce any
                alerts since a price is already entered. Clearly, not all Poodles are the same, so configuring a single
                price for the Poodles can lead to incorrect pricing. When this feature is active the price is set to
                the ‘Grooming work hour rate’ multiplied by the number configured for each breed
                under ‘Setup,’ ‘Basic Services,’ then ‘Grooming,’ and ‘General.’
            </p>
            <p>
                9.2.1.2. We highly recommend the use of the option ‘Use the last non-zero base price as default price.’
                This option can (or not) be used in combination with the option for automatically pricing explained above.
                With this option the price entered for a pet will be carried over to future appointments after they are
                initially configured. Different prices are memorized for Baths and Hair Cuts, and different ‘Grooming Type Modifiers.’
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.4.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <br />
            <p>
                9.2.2. <strong>Grooming type modifiers</strong>
            </p>
            <p>
                * ‘Grooming Type Modifiers’ are sub-categories of Baths and Hair Cuts. Let’s take for example, the ‘Bad Shape’ modifier.
                At the time of reservations, the user can select the reservation to be a ‘Bath,’ a ‘Hair Cut,’ a ‘Bad Shape Bath,’ or a ‘Bad Shape Bath.’
                If using the last non-zero grooming price options, prices for each grooming modifier will be memorized separately.
                Each grooming modifier when selected can adjust the price automatically if the ‘Change Price’ is set to ‘Y.’
                The price adjustment will be calculated by multiplying the ‘Multiplier’ value to the default price.
            </p>
            <p>
                NOTES: <br />
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i> Most business DO NOT use automatic pricing but DO use the last non-zero price options.<br />
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i> We recommend starting with a simple pricing strategy, and as you get more proficient using the software to take advantage of automation and grooming modifiers.<br />
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.5.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <br />
            <hr />
            <h5><strong>Grooming services</strong></h5>
            <p>
                9.3.  Go to "Options" -> "Reservation" -> "Reservation options" -> "Grooming" -> "Services"
            </p>
            <p>
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i>  Summary: ‘Grooming Services’ are add-ons that can be added to a grooming reservation or at any
                            time during the grooming process. ‘Grooming Services’ can have an additional fee that will be added to the base grooming price
                            if desired. The service fee can be configured depending on the pet’s size. For example, a ‘Flee Treatment’ service can be $15
                            for ‘Small Dogs’ and $20 for ‘Large Dogs.’ A breakdown of services will be itemized on the client’s bill so including services
                            that you provide free of charge reminds them of all the work you did on their pet.<br />
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i> Who can skip this step? Nobody. Even business that do not have any additional
                                            grooming services will have to turn off all default services that will not be used.<br />
            </p>
            <p>9.3.1. For the ‘Select type of grooming,’ choose ‘Bath’ or ‘Hair Cut.’</p>
            <p>9.3.2. Enter the service name and price for each pet’s size. If the service is the same price regardless of the
                pet’s size enter the same price in each size column. Make sure the ‘In Use’ column its checked.
                If a service is not needed, simply uncheck the ‘In Use’ column.
                There are a total of 16 different spaces to enter services. The 16 spaces appear in four columns from left
                to right with four in each column. You may overwrite those already there and group similar services together
                or those most often used at the top or in one column.</p>
            <p>
                NOTES: <br />
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i> When scheduling a groom, it will display the services, where you can check mark those you
                                            choose and it will automatically update the price according to what you have set up for that service, i.e.
                                            it will add the service price to the grooming base price. <br />
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i> Don’t leave any columns blank. If a service is not needed, just uncheck the ‘In Use’ column. <br />
            </p>
            <br />
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.6.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
            <br /><br /><br />
            <p>
                9.4. <strong>Grooming commissions</strong> <br />
                Go to "Options" -> "Settings" -> "Commissions"
            </p>
            <p>
                * Summary: in this step all groomer commissions will be configured. Each groomer can have a different
                percentage commission as well as additional bonuses depending on their performance.
                Commissions are fully automatic; you don’t have to do anything except for the initial
                set up. When paying commissions, there is a report available called ‘Grooming Commissions’
                that can be ran between any two dates. <br />
                * Who can skip this step? Single groomers or businesses that do not pay grooming commissions.
            </p>
            <p>
                9.4.1. Under ‘Grooming Commissions’ use the drop down box to select the groomer. Then write the percentage
                commission in that space. If that groomer is not entitled to commissions do not leave the number blank, put 0 (zero) in it.
            </p>
            <p>
                9.4.2.  If you offer an increased % or $ bonus for grooming amount performance over any selected period of time
                continue on and complete the remainder of the ‘Grooming Commissions’ box by selecting the dollar level, the modifier
                as a % or $, and the amount. If this is not needed click on the check marks to remove the defaults.
            </p>
            <p>
                <i class="fa fa-check">&nbsp;</i>
                To search for commissions open up reports, click all reports,
                check commissions under the grooming section and hit Open Reports.
            </p>
            <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.9.7.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
