            <h4>17. Layout setup</h4>
            <hr />
            <p>
                Summary: in this step your facility’s floor plan is configured. <br />
                *     Who can skip this step? Nobody. <br />
                *     How to get here? 'Options' - 'Settings' - 'Layout' <br />
                <br />
                <strong>Layout configuration</strong> <br />
                There are two main steps in the configuration of the layout: (1) the configuration of the ‘Layout Sections’ and the configuration of the ‘Runs.’<br />
                <br />
                Layout Sections:<br />
                <br />
                The ‘Layout Sections’ can be found in the top left of the layout set up screen. Here different areas or buildings are configured.
                There is really no ‘right” way of doing this, it is a matter of choice, of how you want your layout organized.
                Small facilities tend to have one section, while larger facilities usually have multiple sections. At least one section is required (Section 1).<br />
                <br />
                1.      Turn on the ‘In Use’ checkmark for the desired section.<br />
                2.      Enter the desired ‘Section Name’.<br />
                3.      Click ‘Save.’<br />
                <br />
                *     Use sections continuously, i.e. do not skip sections.<br />
                <br />
                <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.17.1.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                <br />
