                    <br />
                    1.      Order multiple copies for each client number. This is useful when a couple want each a different card to access the same account.<br />
                    2.      Consider different types of card, such as key chains. Some clients will only use cards they feel comfortable carrying around.<br />
                    3.      All client numbers should be of the same length (this is required for the system to work properly). For example, if numbers are of length 4, the number 1 would be represented by 0001.<br />
                    <br />
                    <h6>Activate membershitp</h6>
                    <p>
                        Go to "Options" - "Settings" - "User interface", click on the "Enable membership" option, click "Save" <br />
                        <strong>Assing a membership number</strong> <br />
                        1.      Open a client’s file. <br />
                        2.      Click on ‘Membership.’<br />
                        3.      Enter the membership number under ‘Membership.’<br />
                        4.      Enter an expiration date if needed.<br />
                        5.      Click ‘Save.’<br />
                        <br />
                        <strong>Printing a membership card</strong>
                        1.      Open a client’s file. <br />
                        2.      Click on ‘Membership.’ <br />
                        3.      Select ‘Options’, especialy valability, "Save". <br />
                        4.      Click ‘Generate Card.’<br />
                        <br /><br />
                        <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.25.5.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                        <br /><br />
                        <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.25.6.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                        <br />
                    </p>
                </p>
