            <h4>26. Working with pets</h4>
            <hr />
            <p>
                <h5>26.1. Selecting pets</h5>
                <p>
                    A pet can be selected on the client search menu, by "pet name", or by "pet type / breed", "pet_id" <br />
                    (if this searches are activated in "Options" - "Settings" - "General features") <br />
                    Clicking on the client, it will bring a yellow highlight that is selected and will show on right the pet information. <br />
                    Clicking on the wrench icon or on top right "edit", will open the editing of client and pet. <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.1.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>26.2. Adding pets</h5>
                <p>
                    After clicking the edit client button, click "New pet", fill with the new pet information, all fields required then click "save client & pet information" <br />
                    Each client can have / own an unlimited number of pets <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.2.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>26.3. How to mark a pet as deceased</h5>
                <p>
                    Retrieve the pet file, place asterik in front of the pet's name, e.g. *Fluffy, click "save" and the pet will become flagged as such.
                </p>
                <br /><br />
                <h5>26.4. How to delete a pet</h5>
                <p>
                    *     Security Level Management Entry: ‘Delete Client, Pets, Meds & Diets.’ <br />
                    *     Why is important to restrict access to this feature? Once deleted, there is no way to recover the pet’s information. <br />
                    <br />
                    To delete a pet, simply click on the trashcan icon ("delete" button) in the upper right hand corner of the Client/Pet Screen. <br />
                    We strongly recommend that you set to ‘Inactive’ rather than deleting a pet. <br />
                    <br />
                    *     If you don’t see a trashcan icon: that means that you are not allowed to perform that task given your current security level. <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.3.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>26.5. Deal with pet vaccines</h5>
                <p>
                    * Ensure that "vaccinations" are enabled, go to "Options" - "Settings" - "General features", and select he "Vaccinations" checkbox <br />
                    * From the main screen, on top of menu select "Main" <br />
                    * Select / search a client, select pet if multiple, click on the "Vaccinations". Here you select the veterinary and add the vaccines for Rabbies, etc. according
                       to the type of animal, dog / cat. <br />
                    * Veterinary can be edited from "Options" - "Veterinary" <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.4.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>26.6. Change ownership of a pet</h5>
                <p>
                    A pet ownership can be transferred from one client’s record to another. This can happen in many cases such as when a pet is adopted, sold, divorce, etc.
                    To transfer ownership of a pet follow this steps: <br />
                    * Select the client you wish to transfer to, then select the transfered pet and remember or note on a paper the "Client ID" and "Pet ID" on the right screen <br />
                    * Go to "Options" - "Tools" - "Pet ownership" <br />
                    * Here enter the "pet ID" and the new "client ID" then click the check button <br />
                    * Refresh the browser for the changes to take effect <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.5.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>26.7. Pet status</h5>
                <p>
                    * Open for edit a pet file then edit in the screen the "pet status" <br />
                    * You can add / edit / delete multiple pet statuses by going to "Options" - "Pet Options" - "Status" <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.26.6.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
            </p>
