            <h4>27. Working with pet medication or diet</h4>
            <hr />
            <p>
                <h5>27.1. Accessing records</h5>
                <p>
                    1.      Open the pet’s file for which a medication or diet is to be added. <br />
                    2.      On the ‘Pet Screen,’ click on ‘Records.’<br />
                    3.      On the ‘Records’ screen click on ‘Meds’ or ‘Diets.’ <br />
                    4.      Inside, you can toggle between ‘Meds’ and ‘Diets’ screens by changing the value of the dropdown under ‘Search Inventory.’<br />
                </p>
                <h5>27.2. Adding medication or diet to the inventory</h5>
                <p>
                    To add items not currently listed in the inventory:<br />
                    1.      Access the medication or diet screen.<br />
                    2.      Click on ‘Add new Item to Inventory.’<br />
                    3.      Enter the name in the field that appears.<br />
                    4.      Click the check button and the new diet or medication will be listed in the inventory.<br />
                    5.      "X" to exit the inventory <br />
                    <img ng-src="{{'img_help/help.27.1.png' | baseUrl}}" alt="" />
                    <br /><br />
                </p>
                <h5>27.3. Delete a medication or diet</h5>
                <p>
                    * Be carefull, once deleted the medication or diet will no longer appear on records, and will affect reservations as well <br />
                    * Go to "Options" - "Reservations" - "Reservations meds & diets" and select "Meds" or "Diets" <br />
                    * Here you can delete by selecting the "trash icon"<br />
                </p>
                <h5>27.4. Applying a medication or diet to the inventory</h5>
                <p>
                    1.      Open the pet’s file for which a medication or diet is to be applied. <br />
                    2.      On the ‘Pet Screen,’ click on ‘Records.’<br />
                    3.      On the ‘Pet Records’ screen click on ‘Meds’ or ‘Diets.’<br />
                    4.      Select a medication or diet. Typing in the first letters of the medication in the search box will search existing items in inventory.<br />
                    5.      Specify administration times (Morning, Afternoon, Evening and As Needed), amount and type. Selecting ‘Daily’ will add it to every day of the stay. Use ‘On Date’ to add an item to specific dates only.<br />
                    6.      Provide specific dosage/administration instructions and indicate number of charges per day as well as if it is to be given if the pet is only in for Daycare.<br />
                    7.      Click ‘Add Item’ to apply charges.<br />
                </p>
            </p>
